<div id="why-am-i-here" class="panel panel-help">
  <div class="panel-heading">
    <div class="panel-title">Why am I here?</div>
  </div>
  <div class="panel-body">
    <h3>What is Crucendo, and why have I heard so much about it?</h3>
    <p>Those are great questions, let’s start with your first one. Crucendo is a
    way for you to improve yourself a little bit every day. Crucendo will 
    challenge and encourage you with three random questions, then ask you what 
    you have improved recently, followed by what you want to improve in the 
    future. At the end Crucendo will ask you to rate how you’re feeling out of 
    five, and then to finish your Crucendo is a summary of what you achieved by 
    completing it today.</p>
    <p>We recommend that you complete one Crucendo per day, and that you 
    complete your Crucendo at the end of your day. Find a quiet spot, take three
    deep breaths, and give yourself a few minutes to improve (and impress) 
    yourself.</p>
    <p>To answer your second question of why have you heard so much about 
    Crucendo, it’s probably because you’re a social media regular. We’re always 
    on Anchor, Facebook, Instagram, Jelly, LinkedIn, Pinterest, Reddit, 
    Snapchat, Twitter, Vimeo, and YouTube, so there’s a pretty good chance 
    you’ve seen us around.</p>
    <h3>Why should I use Crucendo?</h3>
    <p>Crucendo is something new. You’ve never experienced brilliant software 
    like this, that challenges, encourages, and tracks your development. 
    Crucendo will deliver three questions at random from your various 
    subscriptions, and the questions are designed to make you think about what 
    you’ve been doing recently, so that you can discover development 
    opportunities within yourself. Crucendo will also help you to consider what 
    you’ve improved recently, so that you have a way to reflect on your 
    achievements. Crucendo will also help you to ponder what you want to improve
    in the future, which is a little like setting yourself goals (we call them 
    ‘wants’). In the end you can reflect on your feelings and your mood, and 
    rate yourself on a scale of one to five. One would be an indication that 
    perhaps you’re feeling low or not in a great mood, while five would 
    indicate that things are pretty awesome.</p>
    <p>So let’s recap. You get introspective personal development from the 
    questions, the sense of accomplishment from the ‘haves’ and ‘wants’, and 
    the ability to tie it all to your mood. We feel very confident that 
    Crucendo will be your new best friend, because you deserve the opportunity 
    to impress yourself.</p>
  </div>
